{
  "stem": "6803.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "MG: --full ?] [? of ?] [? life. ?] Were very close.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Everybody knew each other.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Everybody-- in fact, we didn't have no in-- no addresses in our house because we knew exactly where people were living, and who belongs to who, what the family is.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And so we went, and we were-- a happy childhood.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We were-- we-- I liked baseball a lot.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We used to play a lot of baseball.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And when we had time to, that's the only time we had to do it is on a Saturday afternoon.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And because we used to go to cheder, we used to go to school, we were always busy.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And as I said, we were very happy childhood.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, it was against my father's wishes.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But we were, you know, we were young people who wanted to play a little bit.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So we went and played.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Sometimes why-- I got an argument from my father, why I did it, why I didn't come to shul and [INAUDIBLE], and things like that.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It's all right.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We all played truant.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So-- and then, as I-- as I remember in 1940, the Hungarians came in.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they started up the problems, a lot of problems, for the Jewish people.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "People were not allowed to have stores, were not allowed to go to school.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they were not allowed to do anything like human beings should-- should do.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And what happened, what I want to bring out is the-- that in-- in 1944, we got the news-- not through the radio because nobody had any radios or telephones-- through the-- through someone-- loudspeaker that the Jews are not allowed to leave town, not allowed to go on trains, not allowed to leave anywhere.",
      "word_count": 55
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Just stay put where they are.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
